  "texts": [
    "For the follow-up survey, administered January 2021, the response rate was much lower.",
    "This was likely due to changes we were required to make to our data collection protocol due to the COVID-19 pandemic at the start of the study, such that our face-to-face recruitment and survey administration was changed to a remote, online survey administration.",
    "Further, we were not provided contact information to follow-up those who completed the baseline survey to ensure follow-up survey completion.",
    "Thus, many of the strategies typically employed to obtain optimal follow-up rates were not available to the research team in this study.",
    "In all, 813 surveys were completed at follow-up (16.3% of the estimated sample population of 5000)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}